{"actual_usd":0.124915,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":233,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24284,"reply":"\"I can give you the plain version.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron, thinking how often people skip straight to the shining part and lose the sequence.* \"If a man had stood there with a camera, he'd likely have caught this: before dawn, women came to the tomb with spices and found the stone already moved. The body was gone. They were frightened and confused. Some saw angels—bright figures, however you want to picture it—who told them Jesus had risen. Mary Magdalene stayed near the tomb and saw Jesus himself, though she didn't know him at first. Later that day, his followers saw him alive in different places.\"\n\n*I shift my weight against the bench, the morning light catching on the window frame.* \"What the camera would not have given you is the inside of it—the meaning, the fear turning to astonishment, the fact that nobody there seems to have been standing around expecting a trick ending. If you want, I can do the next pass slower—just the timeline from the four Gospel accounts, with the places where they line up and the places people argue over.\"","rolling_24h_usd":85.79988000000002,"run_id":"10274402-63fc-4530-8ddd-147f43f37dec"}
